# FAST.FileManager — S3 Provider HTTP Request Templates
# ======================================================
# Use with: Visual Studio / Rider built-in HTTP client
#           VS Code REST Client extension
#           JetBrains HTTP Client
#     .
# PURPOSE: Replay S3 operations manually to diagnose connection failures
#          against any S3-compatible service (Cloudflare R2, MinIO, AWS, etc.)
#    .
# ── How to use ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Fill in the @variables block below with your credentials and endpoint.
# 2. Run requests top-to-bottom to verify your service supports each operation.
# 3. For signed requests: replace the Authorization header with a live value
#    copied from the Trace log (set log level to Trace in appsettings.json —
#    see the "S3 HTTP diagnostics" comment). Signatures are valid ~15 minutes.
#    .
# ── Path-style vs Virtual-hosted-style ───────────────────────────────────────
# This provider uses PATH-STYLE by default:
#   https://ENDPOINT/BUCKET/KEY
# If your service requires virtual-hosted-style, change the base URL to:
#   https://BUCKET.ENDPOINT/KEY
#   .
# ── Signature note ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# All requests below show the Authorization and x-amz-* headers as placeholders.
# To get a real signed value, enable Trace logging and copy the .http snippet
# that is emitted before each request.
# =============================================================================

@endpoint = http://aafent.runasp.net/FASTFileRepository/s3
@region = auto
@bucket = config
@key = folder/subfolder/file.txt
@source_key = folder/subfolder/file.txt
@dest_key = folder/subfolder/file-copy.txt
@folder_key = folder/subfolder/
@amz_date = 20240101T000000Z
@amz_day = 20240101

@access_key = jsDyoQC1hLdI2YbdWaH0XF9JqfSmJMfZsz2iqkziXDsDuXSacYlcKbVEWwV0yY/4gkeronrBKKff1VFz3ealXiIN0Hz3ZcVAh4VXR6jq/3BnOrXQJRKbDkDuJSrwf/E

# Replace this with the full Authorization header value from the Trace log:
@auth1 = AWS4-HMAC-SHA256 Credential={{access_key}}/{{amz_day}}/{{region}}/s3/aws4_request, SignedHeaders=host;x-amz-content-sha256;x-amz-date, Signature=REPLACE_WITH_LIVE_SIGNATURE
@auth2 = AWS4-HMAC-SHA256 Credential=7c160aac06569d7294c33b2377fe239f/20260603/auto/s3/aws4_request, SignedHeaders=host;x-amz-content-sha256;x-amz-date, Signature=94229d987e140ffe496af9e2658308d7d8bd293838e7e2850c3d96976042c613
@auth = Bearer jsDyoQC1hLdI2YbdWaH0XF9JqfSmJMfZsz2iqkziXDsDuXSacYlcKbVEWwV0yY/4gkeronrBKKff1VFz3ealXiIN0Hz3ZcVAh4VXR6jq/q3BnOrXQJRKbDkDuJSrwf/E


###############################################################################
# 1. LIST BUCKETS
#    GET /
#    Verifies: credentials work, endpoint reachable, service responds with XML
###############################################################################

### List all buckets
GET {{endpoint}}/
x-amz-date: {{amz_date}}
x-amz-content-sha256: e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855
Authorization: {{auth}}


###############################################################################
# 2. LIST OBJECTS V2
#    GET /BUCKET?list-type=2&delimiter=/
#    Verifies: bucket accessible, folder emulation works (CommonPrefixes)
###############################################################################

### List bucket root
GET {{endpoint}}/{{bucket}}?delimiter=/&list-type=2
x-amz-date: {{amz_date}}
x-amz-content-sha256: e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855
Authorization: {{auth}}

### List a specific folder (prefix must end with /)
GET {{endpoint}}/{{bucket}}?delimiter=/&list-type=2&prefix=folder/subfolder/
x-amz-date: {{amz_date}}
x-amz-content-sha256: e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855
Authorization: {{auth}}

### List with pagination (continuation token from previous response)
# GET {{endpoint}}/{{bucket}}?delimiter=/&list-type=2&continuation-token=REPLACE_TOKEN
# x-amz-date: {{amz_date}}
# x-amz-content-sha256: e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855
# Authorization: {{auth}}


###############################################################################
# 3. HEAD OBJECT
#    HEAD /BUCKET/KEY
#    Verifies: object exists, metadata returned (content-type, size, etag)
###############################################################################

### Head object — check metadata without downloading
HEAD {{endpoint}}/{{bucket}}/{{key}}
x-amz-date: {{amz_date}}
x-amz-content-sha256: e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855
Authorization: {{auth}}


###############################################################################
# 4. GET OBJECT (Download)
#    GET /BUCKET/KEY
#    Verifies: object download works, streaming response
###############################################################################

### Download object
GET {{endpoint}}/{{bucket}}/{{key}}
x-amz-date: {{amz_date}}
x-amz-content-sha256: e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855
Authorization: {{auth}}


###############################################################################
# 5. PUT OBJECT (Upload)
#    PUT /BUCKET/KEY
#    Verifies: upload works, UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD accepted by service
#    Note: the provider uses UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD (x-amz-content-sha256: UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD)
#          to avoid buffering. Some services require a real SHA256 — if uploads
#          fail with SignatureDoesNotMatch, this is the likely cause.
###############################################################################

### Upload a small text file
PUT {{endpoint}}/{{bucket}}/{{key}}
x-amz-date: {{amz_date}}
x-amz-content-sha256: UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD
Content-Type: text/plain
Authorization: {{auth}}

Hello from FAST.FileManager test upload.


###############################################################################
# 6. PUT FOLDER MARKER
#    PUT /BUCKET/FOLDER/  (zero-byte, content-type: application/x-directory)
#    Verifies: folder creation works, service accepts empty body with trailing /
###############################################################################

### Create a folder marker
PUT {{endpoint}}/{{bucket}}/{{folder_key}}
x-amz-date: {{amz_date}}
x-amz-content-sha256: e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855
Content-Type: application/x-directory
Content-Length: 0
Authorization: {{auth}}


###############################################################################
# 7. COPY OBJECT
#    PUT /BUCKET/DEST-KEY  with x-amz-copy-source: /BUCKET/SOURCE-KEY
#    Verifies: server-side copy works, x-amz-copy-source header accepted
#    Note: some services (MinIO) require Content-Length: 0 explicitly.
#          The copy-source header uses path-style /bucket/key encoding.
###############################################################################

### Copy object (server-side, no data transfer)
PUT {{endpoint}}/{{bucket}}/{{dest_key}}
x-amz-date: {{amz_date}}
x-amz-content-sha256: e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855
x-amz-copy-source: /{{bucket}}/{{source_key}}
Content-Length: 0
Authorization: {{auth}}


###############################################################################
# 8. DELETE OBJECT
#    DELETE /BUCKET/KEY
#    Verifies: delete works, service returns 204 No Content
###############################################################################

### Delete object
DELETE {{endpoint}}/{{bucket}}/{{key}}
x-amz-date: {{amz_date}}
x-amz-content-sha256: e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855
Authorization: {{auth}}


###############################################################################
# COMMON FAILURE PATTERNS
# ────────────────────────
# 403 SignatureDoesNotMatch  → Wrong AccessKey/SecretKey, wrong Region,
#                              clock skew >5 min, double-encoded URI,
#                              Content-Type included in SignedHeaders but
#                              not sent (or vice versa)
#
# 403 InvalidAccessKeyId    → AccessKey not found — wrong account/endpoint
#
# 404 NoSuchBucket          → Bucket name wrong, wrong endpoint for bucket
#
# 400 AuthorizationHeaderMalformed
#                           → Region mismatch (e.g. "auto" vs "us-east-1")
#                              Try changing @region to match what the service
#                              expects.
#
# 501 NotImplemented        → Service doesn't support this operation
#                              (some MinIO versions don't support CopyObject
#                               the same way as AWS)
#
# Upload fails only         → Service may not accept UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD.
#                              Try replacing x-amz-content-sha256: UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD
#                              with the real SHA256 of the body.
###############################################################################
